ue, malaise, right upper quadrant pain, dark urine, pale stools, and jaundice. Discontinue bedaquiline if aminotransferase elevations are accompanied by total bilirubin elevation greater than 2 times ULN, aminotransferase elevations are greater than 8 times ULN, or aminotransferase elevations persist beyond 2 weeks.', 'Synergism', 'Rifamycin, Miconazole, Polymyxin B, Chloramphenicol, Gentamicin, Chlorhexidine, Neomycin, Tinidazole, Pantoprazole, Dexlansoprazole, Rabeprazole, More', 'Capreomycin, Pyrazinamide, Rifamycin, Sulfamethoxazole, Rifapentine, Streptomycin, Trimethoprim, Rifampicin, Cycloserine, Rifabutin, Isoniazid, More', 'Moderate', NULL, 'DDInter', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/113345/', '[1] "Product Information. Sirturo (bedaquiline)." Janssen Pharmaceuticals, Titusville, NJ.[2] "Product Information. Sirturo (bedaquiline)." Janssen Pharmaceuticals, Titusville, NJ.[3] "Product Information. Hivid (zalcitabine)." Roche Laboratories, Nutley, NJ.', 1767369485);
